A //Lorentz vector space// is $$\mathbb R^{n,1},$$ for $$n\ge 1.$$ The corresponding scalar product ist called a //Lorentz scalar product.//

@@.theorem
''Theorem.''
In a Lorentz vector space, any non-zero vector which is orthogonal to a timelike vector is spacelike.
